    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>People who make or deal in sweet food items such as candy, cakes, icing, and ice cream. Formerly applied to those who compound medicines, poisons, and other drugs, for which now use "pharmacists."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gente que hace o comercia en artículos de alimentos dulces, tales como caramelos, queques, glaseados y helados. Formalmente aplicados a aquellos que combinan medicinas, venenos y otras drogas, para los cuales actualmente se usa "farmacéutico".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Personen die zoete voedingswaren maken of verhandelen, zoals snoep, taarten, glazuur en ijs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
